title: Operations Manager/Instructor/Liaison
description: Direct the daily operations of the only Army operated 24/7 mission for National Security Agency-Colorado (NSA-C). The TCE provides SIGINT support to deployed entities worldwide. Support is provided utilizing a strong foundation of networking, operator training, and operator competence. Supervise 22 joint service personnel through daily communications, direction and guidance, monthly and quarterly evaluations, counseling, mentoring, operations log, and, conflict resolution. Plan, coordinate and execute all training strategies and operational functions. Establish and implement policies, goals, objectives, and procedures through continued job training, weekly meetings, evaluations, and constantly evolving priorities. Liaise with deploying and deployed units, at all echelons, to mitigate intelligence gaps. Provide Combatant Commands and Theater-level programs access to National level resources through multiple communications mediums and classifications to include emails, chat, websites, telephone conference, and databases. Direct and execute daily research, utilizing multiple sources, on political, military, economic and industrial forces in various regions of the world, as well as foreign intelligence threat entities, DoD, and U.S. resources. Disseminate information to multiple personnel in support of operations. Complete Quarterly updates of formal training ensuring relevancy of training based on war fighter needs. Engage all resources, internal and external to the NSA-C, in an effort to gather and disseminate all pertinent intelligence through networking and collaboration. Conduct bi-weekly meetings with senior leadership discussing personnel and equipment requirement and rotations. Regularly asked to brief high level personnel both in person and through video teleconference. Gather facts and use effective analytical and evaluative methods to accurately assess information and make sound decisions.
